    "top_event": "Finger Amputation from Riser Pinch Point",
    "incident_type": "Other Injury",
    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Employee escorted to Medic's office",
      "Employee transported to Terrebonne General Hospital in Houma, Louisiana"
    ],
    "summary": "On November 2, 2014, while inspecting a multiplex (MUX) control line on the riser during BOP stack running operations, a Senior Subsea Engineer had his right index and middle fingertips severed after being caught between the handrail and riser due to riser sway caused by sea state conditions. The incident occurred during the 43rd joint of riser being run. Contributing factors included incomplete Risk Assessment Procedure documentation, failure to address MUX line connection hazards in the Risk Safety Assessment, and poor body placement by the employee.",
